      "acceptanceCriteria": "Systematic review of potential user errors in model setup, boundary condition specification, and post-processing must be documented with error mitigation procedures at MRL 5.",
      "rationale": "Use error assessment was not performed. No formal review of user-introduced errors in boundary condition specification or post-processing of hemolysis index was documented. Flagged as epistemic gap at MRL 5."
    },
    {
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "factorType": "Model form",
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "requiredLevel": 5,
      "achievedLevel": 1,
      "factorStatus": "not-assessed",
      "acceptanceCriteria": "The appropriateness of the hemolysis model form, including turbulence closure and power-law damage accumulation, must be formally justified against alternative model forms with sensitivity analysis at MRL 5.",
      "rationale": "Model form uncertainty was not assessed. No comparison of alternative turbulence models or hemolysis damage models was performed. This is a critical epistemic gap at MRL 5 given the strong influence of model form on absolute hemolysis predictions."
    },
    {
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "factorType": "Model inputs",
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "requiredLevel": 5,
      "achievedLevel": 2,
